==English==

===Etymology===
{{etyl|frm}} ''[[hamelet]]'', diminutive using [[-let]] of ''[[ham]]'' (''village''), of Germanic origin, cognate with [[home]], Dutch [[heem]], German [[Heim]], Old English [[hām]]. (English usage before the 12th century)

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A small [[village]] or a group of houses.
# {{UK}} A village that does not have its own [[church]].
# Any of the fish of the genus ''Hypoplectrus'' in the family ''[[Serranidae]]''.

